                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Why does a file &lt;code&gt;helloworld.py&lt;/code&gt; with just &lt;code&gt;print(&quot;hello world&quot;)&lt;/code&gt; in it can run with command &lt;code&gt;python helloworld.py&lt;/code&gt; even when there is no &lt;code&gt;if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;

