            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;When you run &lt;code&gt;python helloworld.py&lt;/code&gt; it will run the whole script file (whether you specify &lt;code&gt;if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;&lt;/code&gt; or not ) . There is only a difference in execution when you are importing &lt;code&gt;helloworld.py&lt;/code&gt; from a different script. In that case the &lt;code&gt;if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;&lt;/code&gt; codeblock does not execute at all.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
