            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@jpmc26 I&apos;m trying to find an authoritative source that agrees with you. Is this mentioned somewhere?  For example in PEP8 does it say that we should avoid using &lt;code&gt;and&lt;/code&gt; for control purposes, or using &lt;code&gt;or&lt;/code&gt; to assign a default value?  I tried to google it, but I could not find anything.&lt;/span&gt;

