            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;The convention for the ordering of Fibonacci numbers is not entirely set in stone. The usual convention is that the first number is 0, but mathematically this is conventionally &lt;code&gt;F(0)&lt;/code&gt;. You might regard the simple script&apos;s result as an off-by-one error, and fix it accordingly.&lt;/span&gt;

